The paper focuses on developing a deep learning model for pulmonary nodule detection using CT scans, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of a region proposal network, which is commonly used in object detection tasks (cs.AI). The squeeze-and-excitation structure used in the model is a recent development in convolutional neural networks and falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
